## Examples\par
\par
### Basic\par
\par
A simple combobox with a list of frameworks.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-basic" />\par
\par
### Multiple\par
\par
A combobox with multiple selection using `multiple` and `ComboboxChips`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-multiple" />\par
\par
### Clear Button\par
\par
Use the `showClear` prop to show a clear button.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-clear" />\par
\par
### Groups\par
\par
Use `ComboboxGroup` and `ComboboxSeparator` to group items.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-groups" />\par
\par
### Custom Items\par
\par
You can render a custom component inside `ComboboxItem`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-custom" />\par
\par
### Invalid\par
\par
Use the `aria-invalid` prop to make the combobox invalid.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-invalid" />\par
\par
### Disabled\par
\par
Use the `disabled` prop to disable the combobox.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-disabled" />\par
\par
### Auto Highlight\par
\par
Use the `autoHighlight` prop to automatically highlight the first item on filter.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-auto-highlight" />\par
\par
### Popup\par
\par
You can trigger the combobox from a button or any other component by using the `render` prop. Move the `ComboboxInput` inside the `ComboboxContent`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="base-nova" name="combobox-popup" />\par
\par
### Input Group\par
\par
You can add an addon to the combobox by using the `InputGroupAddon` component inside the `ComboboxInput`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="radix-nova" name="combobox-input-group" />\par
